Here is an image of our most recent battery testing:

Screenshot 2023-02-03 2008411891×740 132 KB

We know there is an issue with the discharge rate (A) and with the increments on the AmpHrs on the bottom axis. Because of this, the batteries are being tested for prolonged periods of time which is not very efficient. We are not able to change these settings as well. If anyone knows how we can resolve this issue, it would be greatly appreciated.

Thank you,
Red Watch, Team 2720

Please do not create multiple threads for the same issue, as it makes it harder to find information. Please continue discussion in your existing thread.

Issues with battery testing (CBA III) Technical
Hello, Our team is having issues with the CBA battery analyzer. The software takes a long time to analyze the AmpHr graph, and when the graph finally starts showing the results of the test, it is usually in a straight line. We also used the settings that AndyMark has provided. We are not sure if the issue is with the settings provided or if the software is defective. Any recommendations and suggestions on ways to troubleshoot this issue would be appreciated. Thank you, Red Watch, Team 2720
